Xerium Technologies, Inc. New (NYSE:XRM) Sees Light Trading Volume with 20K Shares Changing Hands 












































 Finance DailyDaily markets, commodities, personal finance and economic newsXerium Technologies, Inc. New (NYSE:XRM) Sees Light Trading Volume with 20K Shares Changing Hands
July 17, 2017 By Ted Blackburn Tweet
        Advertisement



Trading was light with 20K shares changing hands in the last trading session.  Shares saw a steep decrease in trading volume of 90.72% under the normal average daily volume. 
 There has been some selling insider activity on Xerium Technologies, Inc. New (NYSE:XRM) recently.   Jay J. Gurandiano, Director disclosed the sale of 4,000 shares of XRM stock. The shares were sold on May 25th for an average price of $7.01. Gurandiano now owns $342,908 of the stock according to the SEC filing. Jay J. Gurandiano, Director let go of $83,880 worth of shares at an average price of $6.99 on Wed the 3rd. Gurandiano now owns $369,890 of stock as reported to the SEC.
 These funds have also shifted positions in (XRM).   As of quarter end Tower Research Capital LLC (trc) had disposed of  a total of 2,518 shares trimming its holdings by 81.1%. The value of the investment in Xerium Technologies, Inc. New decreased from $17,000 to $4,000 a change of $13,000 quarter over quarter. As of the end of the quarter Goldman Sachs Group Inc had bought 133 shares growing its position 0.6%. The value of the total investment in Xerium Technologies, Inc. New went from $116,000 to $133,000 increasing 14.7% since the last quarter.        Advertisement






 Wynnefield Capital Inc added to its stake by buying 35,000 shares an increase of 3.9%. Wynnefield Capital Inc now holds 935,500 shares worth $5,987,000. The total value of its holdings increased 18.3%. As of quarter end Tpg Group Holdings (sbs) Advisors, Inc. had bought  a total of 234,081 shares growing its stake by 19.8%. The value of the investment in XRM decreased from $9,404,000 to $9,069,000 a change of 3.6% quarter to quarter.
 The company is now up from yesterday’s close of $7.47.  It is currently trading at $7.50 marginally over $7.10, the 50 day moving average and a tad above the 200 day moving average of $6.13.  The 50 day moving average moved up $0.40 and the 200 day average was up $1.37. 
 As of the last earnings report the EPS was $-1.43 and is estimated to be $0.43 for the current year with 16,167,000 shares currently outstanding.  Analysts expect next quarter’s EPS will be $0.11 with next year’s EPS projected to be $0.68. 
 Xerium Technologies, Inc. (Xerium), launched on October 29, 2002, is a manufacturer and supplier of over two types of consumable products used in the production of paper: machine clothing and roll covers. The Company markets its products through brands, such as Huyck Wangner, Weavexx, Stowe Woodward, Mount Hope, Robec and Xibe. The Company operates in two segments: machine clothing and roll covers. Its machine clothing segment products include various types of industrial textiles used on paper-making machines and manufactures spreader rolls. Through its roll covers segment, it manufactures various types of roll covers, refurbishes previously installed roll covers, provides mechanical services for the internal mechanisms of rolls used on paper-making machines, and manufactures spreader rolls. In addition, its products are also installed in other industrial applications, such as non-woven and fiber cement machines..
