Xerium Technologies, Inc. Key Developments

Xerium Technologies, Inc. Wins Orders for Machine Clothing and Rolls Technology for Fibria’s New Pulp Machine at Tres Lagoas Mill in Brazil
May 4 17
Xerium Technologies, Inc. announced that the company was recently awarded orders for machine clothing and rolls technology for Fibria’s new pulp machine at the Tres Lagoas mill in Brazil. The new machine is scheduled to go online in third quarter 2017, adding 1.95 million tons of market pulp to Fibria’s annual production. The growing market pulp segment is a strategic target for the company, whereas the Company has developed specific machine clothing and rolls products designed specifically to support the demanding water handling requirements of these newer machine configurations, and deliver higher production output with lower energy consumption. For this new machine, the company will be supplying ProSeam XT seam felts and DryTrans ND conveyor belts. Additionally, the company will be supplying AquaWell IIS, VersaTec, and Everguard roll cover technology.


Xerium Technologies, Inc., Annual General Meeting, Jun 15, 2017
May 1 17
Xerium Technologies, Inc., Annual General Meeting, Jun 15, 2017, at 10:00 US Eastern Standard Time. Location: at 14101 Capital Boulevard Youngsville, NC 27596 United States Agenda: To elect eight directors; to ratify the appointment of Ernst & Young LLP as company's independent registered public accounting firm; to hold an advisory vote to approve executive compensation. to hold an advisory vote on the frequency of future advisory votes on executive compensation; and to transact such other business as may properly come before the meeting and any adjournment or postponement of the meeting.


Xerium Technologies Inc. Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017; Provides Earnings Guidance for the Year 2017
May 1 17
Xerium Technologies Inc. reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported net sales of $119,866,000 against $114,965,000 a year ago. Income from operations was $14,260,000 against $11,537,000 a year ago. Loss before provision for income taxes was $153,000 against income before provision for income taxes of $1,220,000 a year ago. Net loss was $2,834,000 or $0.18 per basic and diluted share against $1,445,000 or $0.09 per basic and diluted share a year ago. Net cash used in operating activities was $7,223,000 against net cash provided by operating activities of $15,103,000 a year ago. EBITDA was $21,204,000 against $19,555,000 a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was $26,573,000 against $23,935,000 a year ago. Net debt was $524.9 million at the end of first quarter of 2017 compared to $511.7 million at the end of fourth quarter of 2016. The increase in income from operations was driven by higher sales and operational efficiencies. In addition to interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization, adjusted EBITDA excludes expenses related to the company’s restructuring activities, plant start-up costs, stock-based compensation, foreign currency gains and losses and non-recurring expenses.


With an improving market environment and the expected impact of repositioning programs, the company expects 2017 full-year adjusted EBITDA to approximate 2016 levels, or be modestly higher. In addition, the company expects 2017 free cash flow to be modestly lower than the prior year, as higher cash interest and negative currency impacts will not be fully offset by improved operational cash flow.


